<item>
            <title>[LU-324] chgrp can&apos;t be successful to many files</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-324</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a user tried to run chgrp command (recursively) to an directory which has a lot of files (4-5 million files), the client hanged and became no response. They tried a couple of time (even other client), but it couldn&apos;t be successful due to the following errors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Apr 27 10:16:25 t2a006166 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1641802.777783&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Lustre: work0-MDT0000-mdc-ffff880d8ae6c800: Connection to service work0-MDT0000 via nid 10.1.7.17@o2ib was lost; in progress operations using this service will wait for recovery to complete.&lt;br/&gt;
Apr 27 10:16:25 t2a006166 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1641802.777991&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; LustreError: 167-0: This client was evicted by work0-MDT0000; in progress operations using this service will fail.&lt;br/&gt;
Apr 27 10:16:25 t2a006166 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1641802.778116&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; LustreError: 16507:0:(llite_lib.c:1520:ll_setattr_raw()) mdc_setattr fails: rc = -4&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="10860">LU-324</key>
